049923127837417796", "text": "For those who don\u2019t know, $INTC has had specialized fabs for SiPho wafers since 2010s, such as PICs. It divested the transceiver business to Jabil (yes, Intel used to make 100G transceivers\u2026) but retained the wafer (I.e., the PICs) capability. $INTC also manufactured wafers for $TSEM but I remembered a couple of months ago Intel entered negotiation with TSEM to stop that, probably because Intel fabs are fully utilized and transformed to manufacture high-margin server CPUs. $INTC has been a pioneer of R&D in SiPho and recently there was indicators that it will enter the CPO business competing with TSMC", "source": "Twitter for iPhone", "retweetCount": 3, "replyCount": 0, "likeCount": 40, "quoteCount": 0, "viewCount": 3983, "createdAt": "Thu Apr 30 18:45:34 +0000 2026", "lang": "en", "bookmarkCount": 3, "isReply": false, "inReplyToId": null, "conversationId": "2049923127837417796", "displayTextRange": [0, 278], "inReplyToUserId": null, "inReplyToUsername": null, "author": {"type": "user", "userName": "Mar364503", "url": "https://x.com/Mar364503", "twitterUrl": "https://twitter.com/Mar364503", "id": "1700873117411983360", "name": "MQ", "isVerified": false, "isBlueVerified": true, "verifiedType": null, "profilePicture": "https://pbs.twimg.com/profile_images/2004911451610525696/GPMA2m_o_normal.jpg", "coverPicture": "", "description": "Observer | Investor", "location": "", "followers": 629, "following": 93, "status": "", "canDm": false, "canMediaTag": true, "createdAt": "Sun Sep 10 14:05:43 +0000 2023", "entities": {"description": {}}, "fastFollowersCount": 0, "favouritesCount": 883, "hasCustomTimelines": false, "isTranslator": false, "mediaCount": 41, "statusesCount": 1019, "withheldInCountries": [], "affiliatesHighlightedLabel": {}, "possiblySensitive": false, "pinnedTweetIds": ["2014907152247529671"], "profile_bio": {}, "isAutomated": false, "automatedBy": null}, "extendedEntities": {}, "card": null, "place": {}, "entities": {"ha